---
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro'

const emailHref =
  'mailto:winston.j.zhao@gmail.com?subject=AI%20coding%20coaching&body=What%20are%20you%20building%3F%0ACurrent%20tools%3A%0AWhere%20are%20you%20stuck%3F%0A'
---

<BlogLayout
  title="work with me"
  description="1:1 AI coding coaching and workflow setup for business owners building apps"
  pathSegments={[{ name: 'work-with-me', href: null }]}
  backHref="/ston"
>
  <header class="page-header">
    <h1>work-with-me/</h1>
    <p class="page-description">1:1 ai coding coaching for business owners</p>
  </header>

  <section class="hero">
    <h2>build your app and get productive with ai coding</h2>
    <p>
      i help business owners use claude code, codex, and other coding agents to build and maintain
      their apps. we work 1:1 on your real project, set up a workflow you understand, and ship
      something useful together.
    </p>
    <a class="primary-cta" href={emailHref} data-hire-cta="hero">tell me what you're building →</a>
    <p class="availability">1:1 coaching · hands-on setup · remote</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>how i can help</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>set up claude code, codex, your repository, and the tools around them</li>
      <li>teach you how to plan, prompt, review, debug, and ship changes without guessing</li>
      <li>build a real feature with you so the workflow sticks</li>
      <li>add worktrees and parallel agents when they solve a real problem—not because they look impressive</li>
      <li>leave you with a repeatable setup you can keep using on your own</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>this is for you if</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>you run a business and have an app idea, an existing app, or an internal tool to build</li>
      <li>you want to make changes yourself instead of waiting on a developer for every update</li>
      <li>you have tried ai coding tools but keep getting stuck, breaking things, or losing track of the work</li>
      <li>you learn best by working on your own project with someone beside you</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="muted">
      this is coaching and hands-on setup, not a passive course or a full-service development agency.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>why me</h2>
    <p>
      i build apps with coding agents every day. i made
      <a href="https://back2vibing.builtby.win/">back2vibing</a> to manage several agent sessions
      at once, and i write openly about
      <a href="/ston/blog/2026-07-14/parallel-agents-worktrees-tmux">the workflow and where it still breaks</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      before building my own products, i led full-stack and cross-functional projects at doordash,
      including a 15-person engineering and legal effort for the germany launch. i can help with
      both sides: setting up the tools and making sure the work actually ships.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>what happens next</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>email me what you are building, what tools you have tried, and where you are stuck</li>
      <li>we spend 20 minutes deciding whether i can help</li>
      <li>if it fits, i recommend either a focused coaching session or a hands-on setup</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="final-cta">
    <h2>want to build without guessing?</h2>
    <p>bring your app, your idea, or the broken workflow. we will work on the real thing.</p>
    <a class="primary-cta" href={emailHref} data-hire-cta="footer">tell me what you're building →</a>
  </section>
</BlogLayout>

<script is:inline>
  document.querySelectorAll('[data-hire-cta]').forEach((link) => {
    link.addEventListener('click', () => {
      window.posthog?.capture('hire_cta_clicked', {
        cta_location: link.getAttribute('data-hire-cta'),
      })
    })
  })
</script>

<style>
  .page-header,
  .hero,
  section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .page-header h1,
  h2 {
    color: var(--color-term-dir);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .page-description,
  .availability,
  .muted {
    color: var(--color-term-fg-muted);
  }

  .page-description,
  .availability {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .hero {
    border-left: 2px solid var(--color-term-dir);
    padding-left: 1rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  p,
  li {
    font-size: 0.925rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  p {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  ul,
  ol {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }

  ul {
    list-style: disc;
  }

  ol {
    list-style: decimal;
  }

  li + li {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  a {
    color: var(--color-term-link);
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .primary-cta {
    display: inline-block;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0.75rem;
    padding: 0.7rem 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-term-bg);
    background: var(--color-term-dir);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-term-dir);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .primary-cta:hover,
  .primary-cta:focus-visible {
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--color-term-dir);
  }

  .muted {
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .final-cta {
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-term-bg-lighter);
  }

  @media (max-width: 40rem) {
    .primary-cta {
      display: block;
      text-align: center;
    }
  }
</style>
